**Meilisearch version:**[1.11]

While using Meilisearch for vectorization, I encountered the following error
```
thread 'embedding-request-14' has overflowed its stack
fatal runtime error: stack overflow
```
The request I executed：
```
curl --location --request PATCH 'http://10.8.2.70:7006/indexes/spp_doc/settings' \
--header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
--data '{
    "embedders": {
        "default": {
            "source": "rest",
            "url": "http://10.8.2.70:7005/v1/embeddings",
            "documentTemplate": "标题:{{doc.title}};工艺描述:{{doc.step_content}}",
            "documentTemplateMaxBytes": 10000,
            "dimensions": 1024,
            "request": {
                "model": "host-bge-large-zh-v1.5",
                "input": "标题:{{doc.title}};工艺描述:{{doc.step_content}}",
                "prompt": "{{text}}"
            },
            "response": {
                "data": [
                    {
                        "embedding": "{{embedding}}"
                    }
                ]
            }
        }
    }
}'
```

This error occurs during the vectorization process. However, as shown in picture, using docker stats I found that the memory usage is well below the available limit, indicating that there is sufficient memory.

![dba987e31941000e837393fdc1da960](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/ae38a0fe-463e-486a-ab9e-207f4dc71f89)

Additionally, I'm processing a dataset with 450,000 entries. Previously, version 1.8 handled the same data without any issues.

Despite the ample memory, the stack overflow error persists. I'm unsure why this is happening when there seems to be plenty of available resources.

Has anyone faced a similar issue or knows how to resolve this stack overflow error with Meilisearch? Any guidance or suggestions would be greatly appreciated
